      • setOutputFields

        public T setOutputFields(int value)
        Sets what parking lot information should be returned.

        The default value is ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_BASIC. Supported values are:

        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_BASIC
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_PRICING
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_GEOMETRY
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_DYNAMIC
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_STATIC
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_ALL

        Fields can be combined. For instance, to return both basic information and pricing, use PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_BASIC | PARKING_OUTPUT_FIELD_PRICING.

        Parameters:
        value - Fields to return for parking lot information.
        Returns:
        This instance of the class.
        Throws:
        ParkingManager.ParkingManagerException - when value is invalid.

      • setCount

        public T setCount(int value)
        The maximum number of results.

        NOTE: If setParkingType(int) set to both ParkingManager.PARKING_TYPE_PARKING_LOT and ParkingManager.PARKING_TYPE_PARKING_BLOCK, count is applied to each subset independently.

        For instance, if count set to 10, response will return 10 parking lots and 10 parking blocks, if available.

        Parameters:
        value - Number of results.
        Returns:
        Current instance.

      • setParkingType

        public T setParkingType(int type)
        Sets the requested parking types. Can be a combination of:
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_TYPE_PARKING_LOT
        • ParkingManager.PARKING_TYPE_PARKING_BLOCK

        Default value is ParkingManager.PARKING_TYPE_PARKING_LOT.
